WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.040
Chapter 5 Hellen has two loves

00:04.800 --> 00:10.160
Hermia was looking for Lysander. It was very dark and she was afraid.

00:11.040 --> 00:18.640
She called his name many times. There was no answer. After a few hours she saw someone

00:18.640 --> 00:24.320
and she began to feel happy. But it wasn't Lysander. It was Demetrius.

00:24.400 --> 00:28.240
Demetrius saw her and he smiled.

00:29.680 --> 00:38.240
Hermia, my love, I found you. He said, come with me. We need to go back to Athens. We need to get

00:38.240 --> 00:41.040
married. Hermia wanted to cry.

00:42.320 --> 00:47.200
Where is Lysander? She asked. Lysander? Said Demetrius.

00:48.080 --> 00:54.000
I don't know. Forget about Lysander. You're going to be my wife, not his.

00:55.120 --> 01:01.680
She suddenly felt afraid. Demetrius. Did you hurt Lysander?

01:01.680 --> 01:09.200
She said. Did you kill him? Me. No. Said Demetrius.

01:10.560 --> 01:16.640
Oberon and Puck were near Hermia and Demetrius. They were still laughing about Portitania.

01:18.080 --> 01:22.480
Yes. Good work, Puck. Said Oberon.

01:23.920 --> 01:29.520
And did you help the young lady from Athens? Did you put the juice of the flower on the man's eyes?

01:30.480 --> 01:39.520
Yes, of course. It was easy. Said Puck. Oberon looked through the trees. He saw Demetrius and Hermia.

01:40.560 --> 01:43.200
That's strange. He said?

01:44.080 --> 01:50.560
There's the young man, but he's not with the right woman. They listened to Demetrius and Hermia.

01:51.520 --> 01:58.000
Listen to me, Demetrius. Hermia was saying. I don't love you. I'll never love you.

01:58.880 --> 02:04.560
Don't say that, Hermia. Said Demetrius. I don't want to see you ever again.

02:05.440 --> 02:13.120
Said Hermia. She walked away into the wood. Demetrius watched her. I can't follow her.

02:13.360 --> 02:20.160
She's too angry, he thought. Demetrius sat down on the grass. He put his head in his hands.

02:22.400 --> 02:26.720
It's true, he thought. She doesn't love me at all.

02:27.280 --> 02:32.800
Demetrius felt very sad and very tired. In a few minutes, he was asleep.

02:34.240 --> 02:40.640
Oberon was starting to feel angry. Puck, you chose the wrong man. He said?

02:41.440 --> 02:48.720
Did I? Said Puck. Go and find Helena. Said Oberon.

02:49.920 --> 02:56.800
She's a tall girl with red hair. Find her and bring her to this place. Go now.

02:58.480 --> 03:05.280
Puck flew away quickly. He was afraid of Oberon. Oberon looked at Demetrius.

03:05.920 --> 03:12.080
He put the juice of the magic flower on his eyes. Now you will love Helena.

03:12.080 --> 03:21.680
He said? You will only love Helena. In a few minutes, Puck came back. He was laughing.

03:24.480 --> 03:31.840
Here she is, my king. Helena is coming. He said? But she's not alone.

03:32.800 --> 03:36.320
It was true. My sander was following Helena.

03:37.200 --> 03:42.720
My love, wait for me. Said Lysander. I need to be near you.

03:43.760 --> 03:52.080
Helena was very angry now. For the last time, this isn't funny. Stop joking and leave me alone.

03:52.800 --> 04:00.480
She shouted. Just then, Demetrius opened his eyes. He saw a very beautiful young woman.

04:01.200 --> 04:09.200
Was it a fairy or a princess? No, it was Helena. Did I really run away from her?

04:10.320 --> 04:17.600
Demetrius thought? I was very wrong. She's wonderful. He stood up suddenly.

04:18.480 --> 04:24.800
Helena? He shouted. My love, my queen. I want to kiss you.

04:25.680 --> 04:35.040
Helena screamed. Oh, no! She said? Not you two. Now you're both laughing at me.

04:39.120 --> 04:44.480
She began to cry. Yes, Demetrius. Said Lysander.

04:44.480 --> 04:53.040
Don't joke. Everyone knows that you love Hermia. Well, I have good news for you. She's yours.

04:54.000 --> 05:01.440
I only love Helena. Lysander took Helena's hand. Keep your Hermia.

05:03.440 --> 05:12.400
Said Demetrius. This is my true love. He took Helena's other hand. They both pulled on Helena's arms.

05:13.120 --> 05:19.840
Stop it! Shouted Helena. At that moment, Hermia was walking somewhere near the wood.

05:20.560 --> 05:28.080
She heard voices. Is it Lysander? She thought? Yes, it's him. He's safe.

05:29.200 --> 05:31.520
She ran towards the voices of her friends.

05:36.080 --> 05:44.000
Chapter 6. Fighting. Hermia ran towards Lysander and she put her arms around him.

05:44.880 --> 05:57.280
Lysander, you're safe. She said. But why did you leave me? I was all alone. I thought something terrible happened to you.

05:57.840 --> 06:08.080
Lysander's eyes were cold. He turned away from her. I left because of love. He said. Hermia didn't understand.

06:09.040 --> 06:13.840
What do you mean? You love me. She said. You?

06:17.200 --> 06:29.280
Lysander laughed. No. I don't love you. I love Helena. Helena was watching them. She felt very hurt and angry.

06:30.240 --> 06:38.720
Oh, now I see. Helena said. She's part of this joke too. Was this your idea, Hermia?

06:40.000 --> 06:47.680
What are you talking about? What joke? Asked Hermia. You know very well. Said Helena.

06:48.560 --> 06:58.240
I know Demetrius doesn't love me. Do you really think it's funny? You're my best friend. Why are you doing this to me?

06:59.280 --> 07:08.800
No, Helena. You're wrong. Said Hermia. I don't know anything about a joke. Lysander, stop this. Don't laugh at Helena.

07:09.600 --> 07:17.440
Yes. Don't even talk to her, Lysander. Said Demetrius. I'll fight you now. Helena's mine.

07:18.000 --> 07:27.280
Yes. I'll fight you. Right now. Said Lysander. But Hermia stopped him. She held his arms.

07:28.000 --> 07:34.240
Don't do it, Lysander. She said. He'll hurt you. Stay here with me.

07:35.600 --> 07:39.360
Lysander tried to get away from her. Demetrius laughed.

07:41.520 --> 07:50.400
Helena thought it was all part of the joke. Let go of me. Lysander shouted at Hermia. Why are you here?

07:51.040 --> 07:57.920
I don't want you. Lysander. I don't understand this. Said Hermia.

07:58.720 --> 08:05.360
Are you joking? Yes, he is. And you're joking too. Said Helena angrily.

08:06.160 --> 08:17.840
Joking? Said Lysander. No. Why can't you understand? I don't love you. I'm starting to hate you.

08:18.800 --> 08:28.080
And I love Helena. Hermia let go of Lysander. She felt sad and very surprised.

08:29.440 --> 08:36.640
It's true. She thought. He doesn't love me at all. Then she turned to Helena.

08:38.320 --> 08:46.080
You? She said in a loud angry voice. Why does he love you now? What did you do to him?

08:46.960 --> 08:53.200
I didn't do anything. Said Helena. She was starting to feel afraid of her friend.

08:53.920 --> 09:02.320
You stole him from me. I'll fight you. Said Hermia. She ran towards Helena. Help!

09:03.440 --> 09:11.920
Said Helena. She hid behind Demetrius and Lysander. I know her. She's small, but she's dangerous.

09:12.880 --> 09:23.920
Small. You think I'm short. Said Hermia. I'm not short. You're too tall. Come here. Fight me.

09:24.800 --> 09:30.960
Lysander stood between Hermia and Helena. Leave her alone, you little cat.

09:31.440 --> 09:39.760
He said to Hermia. Stay away from my beautiful Helena. She's not yours. Said Demetrius.

09:40.640 --> 09:48.400
Come and fight me. Let's go over there. The prize will be beautiful Helena. Yes. Let's go.

09:48.400 --> 09:56.560
Said Lysander. He turned and followed Demetrius into the wood. Hermia did not try to stop him this time.

09:57.360 --> 10:04.160
Helena and Hermia were alone together for a moment. Helena looked at Hermia's angry face.

10:04.640 --> 10:10.640
Then she quickly ran away into the wood. Now, Hermia was alone.

10:11.680 --> 10:17.520
I don't understand this. She thought. What's happening to us?

10:17.520 --> 10:25.040
At the same time, Oberon and Puck were watching everything. Oberon was very angry.

10:26.320 --> 10:33.360
Did you do this, Puck? He said. I think it's funny. Said Puck.

10:34.400 --> 10:38.800
Well, you must make everything right again. Said Oberon.

10:40.000 --> 10:45.040
Find the two men. Keep them away from each other. They must not fight.

10:46.480 --> 10:54.400
Oberon gave Puck some small green leaves. There were leaves from a magic plant. This plant could

10:54.400 --> 11:02.560
change the magic of the purple flower. When they fall asleep, put the juice of this plant on Lysander's

11:02.640 --> 11:12.320
eyes. The magic will leave him. Go. Yes, my king. Said Puck. He flew away into the night.

11:16.880 --> 11:26.400
Listening activity. Ali? What are you doing here alone? Why aren't you with your friends?

11:27.200 --> 11:34.880
What friends? You have lots of friends. What about Susan? She's your best friend.

11:35.680 --> 11:40.560
She was. Now she never calls me on the phone and she never emails.

11:41.440 --> 11:46.640
Oh. Well, there's still David. He's a nice boy. Or Mike.

11:47.200 --> 11:55.200
No way. David took my favorite CD and he won't give it back. And when I try to do anything with Mike,

11:55.280 --> 12:00.160
he's never on time. I waited for him for two hours last time.

12:00.160 --> 12:08.160
Okay. What about Laura then? I'm not talking to her. She said bad things about me to other people.

12:08.160 --> 12:13.680
She's always doing that. There's Claire. You like Claire, don't you?

12:13.680 --> 12:21.760
No, I don't. She's so boring. Always talking and talking about nothing. Who has time for that?

12:22.720 --> 12:30.240
What about the neighbor's girl, Eleanor? No, I try to be friends with her, but she doesn't like me.

12:30.240 --> 12:36.240
She doesn't like anybody. Oh. Would you like to do something with me then?

12:37.840 --> 12:40.800
Well, okay, Dad.

12:40.800 --> 12:48.320
Chapter 7. The End of the Magic.

12:50.800 --> 12:56.800
Lysander ran through the wood. He was very angry and he wanted to fight Demetrius.

12:57.600 --> 13:03.040
But where was he? He could hear Demetrius' voice, but he couldn't see him.

13:04.400 --> 13:08.960
Lysander didn't know it, but the voice was not really the voice of Demetrius.

13:09.920 --> 13:15.280
It was Park's voice. He was using his magic to speak in Demetrius' voice.

13:16.560 --> 13:20.240
Lysander couldn't see him, but he followed him everywhere.

13:21.360 --> 13:24.960
Come on. Park said in Demetrius' voice,

13:26.000 --> 13:28.400
Fight me. Are you afraid?

13:29.440 --> 13:33.520
I'm not afraid. Said Lysander. Where are you?

13:33.520 --> 13:42.000
The voice was always in front of him. He ran and ran. He followed the voice all over the wood.

13:42.000 --> 13:51.280
After several hours, Lysander was very tired. He couldn't run. He couldn't even walk. He laid

13:51.280 --> 14:00.160
down on the grass near a river and fell asleep. Then Park did the same thing to Demetrius. He flew

14:00.240 --> 14:08.320
in front of Demetrius and spoke in Lysander's voice. Demetrius ran for hours. But of course,

14:08.320 --> 14:13.840
he never found Lysander. He followed Park to the same place where Lysander was sleeping.

14:14.960 --> 14:22.240
It was dark, and so he didn't see him. By then Demetrius was also very, very tired.

14:23.440 --> 14:28.160
He laid down on the grass and fell asleep, not far from Lysander.

14:29.040 --> 14:36.400
Next, Park looked for Helena and Hermia. They were both walking in different parts of the wood

14:36.400 --> 14:45.120
by themselves, and they were both very tired and sad. Park used his magic, and they followed him

14:45.120 --> 14:51.600
to the place where Lysander and Demetrius were sleeping. First, Helena arrived and went to sleep,

14:52.480 --> 14:58.400
and then Hermia did the same. Park looked at the four friends, and he laughed.

15:00.240 --> 15:03.520
Then he put the juice of the magic leaves on Lysander's eyes.

15:04.880 --> 15:12.640
The magic will leave you, said Park. You think that this night was just a dream?

15:13.840 --> 15:21.120
Then Park flew away. He wanted to tell Oberon the good news. Soon he found Oberon.

15:21.840 --> 15:27.440
Not far from the place where the four friends were sleeping. Oberon had a new servant with him.

15:28.160 --> 15:30.080
It was the beautiful Indian boy.

15:31.280 --> 15:38.960
Did Tanya gave you the boy? Park said. You won. But Oberon did not look happy.

15:40.400 --> 15:48.320
Yes, she gave me the boy very easily. She forgot that we were arguing. She forgot about me.

15:49.200 --> 15:56.960
She can only think about that monster. He pointed at Titanya and Bottom. They were sitting under a

15:56.960 --> 16:03.840
large tree. Titanya was looking at Bottom's horrible face and smiling.

16:05.040 --> 16:11.920
What do you want, my dear? She said in her soft voice. Some music? Flowers?

16:12.880 --> 16:18.400
Titanya's fairy servants came. They sang and played beautiful music for Bottom.

16:19.520 --> 16:24.480
Some fairies brought flowers. And Titanya put them around Bottom's big ears.

16:25.840 --> 16:29.360
And what would you like to eat? Asked Titanya.

16:30.320 --> 16:41.520
Oh, I'd like some grass, please. Some nice tall grass. Or I could eat these flowers.

16:42.880 --> 16:45.920
He said Bottom in his strange donkey's voice.

16:47.120 --> 16:52.400
Anything? Said Titanya. She looked at Bottom and smiled.

16:53.200 --> 17:02.480
You're so beautiful. Your eyes. Your voice. Your wonderful ears. I love you so much.

17:03.920 --> 17:10.080
Bottom ate a good meal of grass and flowers. And then he and Titanya fell asleep under the tree.

17:11.040 --> 17:12.640
The fairies sang to them.

17:14.720 --> 17:16.800
Oberon looked at Titanya and Bottom.

17:18.240 --> 17:25.520
I thought it was funny at first. He said to Park. But now I'm sorry. It's time to stop the magic.

17:26.720 --> 17:32.080
He put the magic leaves on Titanya's eyes. And the magic of the flower left her.

17:33.040 --> 17:36.880
Wake up, my queen. Oberon said softly.

17:37.840 --> 17:39.920
Titanya woke up and smiled.

17:41.360 --> 17:49.120
Oberon, I had such a strange dream. In my dream, I loved a monster.

17:49.680 --> 17:53.280
She said. Then she saw Bottom and she screamed.

17:54.400 --> 17:56.720
Oh, he's horrible.

17:58.080 --> 18:02.720
She jumped up and hit her face. Oberon put his arms around her.

18:03.600 --> 18:07.360
The bad dreams are over, my love. He said.

18:09.280 --> 18:15.680
It's almost time for Theseus and Hippolyta's wedding. We must go to Athens. We'll bring good luck to

18:15.680 --> 18:23.760
Theseus and Hippolyta at their wedding tomorrow. Oberon called Park and spoke to him. Park used

18:23.760 --> 18:30.800
his magic and he took the donkey's head away from Bottom. Then Oberon and Titanya walked through

18:30.800 --> 18:39.040
the wood together. Titanya saw Lysander, Demetrius, Helena and Hermia on the grass. And she laughed.

18:41.360 --> 18:48.000
Who are they? She asked. They are four friends who had a very bad night and they need to sleep.

18:48.960 --> 18:55.040
Said Oberon. Titanya called her servants. Sing to them fairies.

18:55.680 --> 19:03.840
She said. They must sleep until the morning. The fairies sang and played music and the four

19:03.840 --> 19:16.960
friends slept all night. Listening activity. Hello, seaside dinner theatre. Can I help you?

19:18.000 --> 19:24.880
Yes. I want to see the play tonight and have dinner. Good. Can I have your name, please?

19:26.000 --> 19:39.840
My last name is Farrell. That's F-A-R-R-E-L-L. Thank you, Miss Farrell. How many people are going?

19:40.560 --> 19:45.280
There will be four of us. Okay. The play starts at eight o'clock.

19:46.000 --> 19:54.320
Good. What's the play again? I forget. A Midsummer Night's Dream. It's a great show. You'll love it.

19:55.360 --> 20:00.320
But that's a very long play. Isn't it three or four hours?

20:00.320 --> 20:07.200
Oh, we're not showing the whole play. Just the best parts. The show will be over at 10 o'clock.

20:07.840 --> 20:16.960
Okay. Now, how much is that going to be? That will be £120. You can pay at the door.

20:17.520 --> 20:25.200
Really? I didn't think it was so expensive. Oh, sorry. That's all the tickets together.

20:25.760 --> 20:32.000
It's £30 for each ticket. And the ticket is for the play and dinner.

20:32.000 --> 20:38.400
That's much better. Okay. Thank you very much. Thank you. Enjoy the show.

20:39.360 --> 20:40.400
Just a moment.

20:40.400 --> 20:41.360
Hello?

20:48.400 --> 20:51.280
Acting in theatres in Shakespeare's time.

20:52.000 --> 20:57.120
400 years ago during Shakespeare's life, theatres and acting were very different.

20:57.120 --> 21:02.400
First, there were no actresses. Boy is acted as the young women in Shakespeare's plays.

21:02.880 --> 21:26.800
At the end of a Midsummer Night's Dream, Duke Thesis watches a play at his home.

21:26.800 --> 21:36.000
Theatres were also very different. The theatres were large. Almost 3000 people could see a play at the same time.

21:37.280 --> 21:40.960
If these people didn't like the play, they usually made a lot of noise.

21:42.320 --> 21:48.560
The theatres also usually had no roofs. When it rained, the people who watched the plays got wet.

21:49.760 --> 21:55.680
And this was in England, where it often rains. Many people had to stand up for the whole play.

21:57.040 --> 22:02.480
People who paid more for a ticket could sit down. All of the plays started in the afternoon.

22:03.360 --> 22:09.200
There were no special lights. Most of the story in a Midsummer Night's Dream happens at night,

22:09.840 --> 22:14.320
but the actors of Shakespeare's times probably performed in the afternoon sun.

22:15.920 --> 22:20.560
Shakespeare's favourite theatre was The Globe, which burned down in 1613.

22:21.520 --> 22:25.760
In 1996, some people in London built a copy of this theatre.

22:26.720 --> 22:32.560
They built this copy at the same place where The Old Globe stood and it is just like The Old Theatre.

22:33.600 --> 22:35.920
Go and see a play there when you are in London.

22:40.400 --> 22:42.800
Chapter 8 Three Weddings

22:42.800 --> 22:52.000
Hermia, Helena, Lysander and Demetrius continued to sleep. The morning came and then it was noon.

22:52.880 --> 22:58.160
The wood was quiet. Then suddenly there was the noise of horses and people.

22:59.040 --> 23:03.360
It was Theseus and Hippolyta with their servants and some of their friends.

23:04.160 --> 23:11.600
Ageus, Hermia's father, was with them. They were hunting in the wood. They all stopped when they saw

23:11.600 --> 23:13.280
the four young people on the grass.

23:14.560 --> 23:17.680
That's my daughter, said Ageus.

23:18.240 --> 23:23.120
What is she doing here? And Lysander and Demetrius.

23:24.000 --> 23:31.760
Wake them, said Thesis, and his servants blew their horns. The four young people woke up and looked

23:31.760 --> 23:34.320
around. They were very surprised.

23:34.560 --> 23:40.960
What are you all doing here, said Thesis? Lysander stood up.

23:41.600 --> 23:49.840
I came here with Hermia. We wanted to run away together. I love her very much. And I want to marry her.

23:50.400 --> 23:52.880
He said, Hermia smiled.

23:53.840 --> 23:55.840
So he doesn't love Helena?

23:56.320 --> 23:57.360
She thought.

23:57.360 --> 23:59.520
It was all a dream.

23:59.920 --> 24:01.920
But Ageus was very angry.

24:01.920 --> 24:03.840
Never, he said.

24:03.840 --> 24:09.280
Hermia, you're going to marry Demetrius. Isn't that right, Demetrius?

24:10.240 --> 24:16.880
Demetrius stood up. He spoke to Ageus. But he looked only at Helena.

24:17.600 --> 24:24.640
I'm sorry, sir, but it's not true. I did love Hermia, but that love is gone.

24:25.040 --> 24:28.320
Now I love Helena, and I will always love her.

24:32.000 --> 24:38.400
Finally, Helena understood that Demetrius was not joking. She wanted to cry with happiness.

24:39.200 --> 24:41.200
She put her arms around Demetrius.

24:41.920 --> 24:44.000
Well, said Thesis.

24:45.600 --> 24:51.520
Then there will be three weddings today and not just one. Come back to Athens and we will all

24:51.520 --> 24:59.200
celebrate together. They all went back to the city. On the way, the four friends talked about

24:59.200 --> 25:04.960
their strange dream. At the same time, Bottom was still asleep under the tree.

25:05.760 --> 25:07.840
He woke up suddenly and looked around.

25:09.360 --> 25:11.520
What a dream, he thought.

25:12.480 --> 25:15.200
Strange and wonderful.

25:16.080 --> 25:19.600
He remembered the donkey's head and the beautiful fairy queen.

25:20.800 --> 25:25.600
I'll tell Peter Quince about my dream. He can write a song about it.

25:26.400 --> 25:28.240
I can sing it for Thesis.

25:29.280 --> 25:30.800
Then he remembered the wedding.

25:32.000 --> 25:33.200
Thesis is wedding.

25:33.200 --> 25:34.240
He shouted.

25:34.240 --> 25:36.960
The play. I have to find my friends.

25:37.760 --> 25:39.600
Bottom ran towards the city.

25:40.720 --> 25:44.320
The three weddings were full of music and dancing and flowers.

25:44.960 --> 25:51.200
Even Ageus was happy. After the weddings, there was another party at Thesis's beautiful house.

25:52.400 --> 25:54.240
Thesis decided to watch the play.

25:55.680 --> 25:57.920
Bottom's friends were at Peter Quince's house.

25:58.640 --> 26:02.800
They were trying to practice, but the play needed a hero.

26:03.920 --> 26:05.440
And someone came to the door.

26:06.400 --> 26:09.760
It was Thesis's servant and he had a letter for them.

26:10.720 --> 26:12.480
Peter Quince read the letter.

26:13.600 --> 26:15.760
Then he sat down with his head in his hands.

26:16.560 --> 26:18.320
This is terrible news.

26:19.120 --> 26:19.680
He said,

26:20.640 --> 26:25.040
The Duke wants to see our play, but we can't do the play without Bottom.

26:25.680 --> 26:27.200
Who be our hero?

26:28.080 --> 26:30.400
I will, said a voice at the door.

26:31.280 --> 26:34.240
They all turned to look. It was Bottom.

26:34.800 --> 26:35.280
Bottom!

26:36.800 --> 26:37.520
You're safe.

26:38.560 --> 26:39.920
You're not a monster.

26:40.960 --> 26:44.480
His friend said, and they all put their arms around him.

26:45.120 --> 26:46.240
Bottom smiled.

26:47.120 --> 26:50.480
Does Thesis really want to see our play?

26:51.120 --> 26:51.680
He said.

26:52.560 --> 26:54.240
Then we don't have much time.

26:54.800 --> 26:55.760
Let's get ready.

26:56.880 --> 27:03.600
Thesis, Hippolyta, Lysander, Hermia, Helena and Demetrius all watched the play together.

27:04.480 --> 27:07.120
Bottom and his friends made a lot of mistakes,

27:07.680 --> 27:10.960
and sometimes Lysander or Demetrius laughed.

27:11.680 --> 27:13.600
But the actors tried very hard.

27:14.400 --> 27:17.840
Afterwards, Thesis gave them a large bag of gold.

27:18.720 --> 27:22.400
They were all very happy, but the happiest was Bottom.

27:23.520 --> 27:25.360
Soon it was time to go to bed.

27:26.080 --> 27:27.840
The moon was high in the sky.

27:28.640 --> 27:30.080
Everyone fell asleep.

27:31.200 --> 27:35.440
Then Titania, Oberon, Puck and all the fairies arrived.

27:36.320 --> 27:38.480
They danced through all the rooms of the house.

27:39.040 --> 27:41.040
They danced until morning.

27:41.040 --> 27:45.440
They brought good luck to the house, and good luck to everyone who slept there.

27:49.280 --> 27:50.720
A mid-summer night's dream

27:52.640 --> 27:54.080
by William Shakespeare.

27:55.760 --> 27:58.400
Copyright Black Cat Publishing.

28:11.680 --> 28:13.680
William Shakespeare

28:15.680 --> 28:20.400
Most people think that William Shakespeare is the greatest writer in the English language,

28:20.960 --> 28:22.880
but we don't know much about his life.

28:23.520 --> 28:28.080
He was born in the town of Stratford upon Avon in Central England,

28:28.080 --> 28:31.520
probably on the 23rd of April 1564.

28:32.480 --> 28:37.200
His father was a glovemaker, and his mother was the daughter of a rich farmer.

28:38.320 --> 28:40.640
William had seven brothers and sisters.

28:41.600 --> 28:46.800
He went to school and studied Greek and Latin, and the works of many famous poets.

28:48.400 --> 28:53.360
When he was 18, he married Anne Hathaway, who was eight years older than him.

28:54.160 --> 28:55.360
They had three children.

28:56.160 --> 29:03.840
Susanna was born in 1582, and Hamnet and Judith, who were twins, were born in 1585.

29:05.360 --> 29:07.760
William went to live in London a few years later,

29:08.240 --> 29:11.520
but Anne and the children stayed in Stratford upon Avon.

29:12.640 --> 29:17.280
In London, Shakespeare became an actor, and later he became a writer.

29:18.160 --> 29:23.920
He wrote 40 plays and many poems between 1592 and 1613.

29:25.280 --> 29:31.040
Some of his most famous plays were Hamnet, Romeo and Juliet, and King Lear.

29:32.160 --> 29:35.920
He wrote a mid-summer night's dream in 1595.

29:38.000 --> 29:41.040
Shakespeare's plays were popular, and he became rich.

29:41.760 --> 29:45.040
He bought a good house in Stratford upon Avon for his family,

29:45.920 --> 29:48.000
but there were sad times as well.

29:48.800 --> 29:54.400
His son, Hamnet, died in 1596 when he was only 11 years old.

29:55.840 --> 30:00.480
Some people also think that Shakespeare and Anne Hathaway were not happy together.

30:02.080 --> 30:06.560
Near the end of his life, Shakespeare moved back to his home in Stratford upon Avon.

30:07.520 --> 30:12.480
He died there on the 23rd of April 1616, on his birthday.

30:14.160 --> 30:18.320
Now people read and study Shakespeare's plays and poems everywhere.

30:19.280 --> 30:23.120
People still perform his plays all over the world,

30:23.120 --> 30:26.720
and there are also hundreds of films of Shakespeare's plays.

30:26.720 --> 30:32.560
Listening activity.

30:34.080 --> 30:34.800
Example.

30:36.080 --> 30:37.280
Titania.

30:39.760 --> 30:40.080
One.

30:42.080 --> 30:43.040
Lysander.

30:45.200 --> 30:45.440
Two.

30:47.280 --> 30:48.320
Demetrius.

30:50.960 --> 30:51.280
Three.

30:53.200 --> 30:53.840
Hermia.

30:54.480 --> 30:55.440
Four.

30:56.400 --> 30:57.040
Theseus.

30:58.960 --> 30:59.360
Five.

31:00.960 --> 31:01.440
Hippolyta.

31:04.240 --> 31:05.280
Chapter one.

31:06.240 --> 31:08.240
Trouble in Athens.

31:10.000 --> 31:14.640
Everyone in the city of Athens was getting ready for a wonderful celebration.

31:15.280 --> 31:21.200
In a few days, their duke, Theseus, was going to marry the beautiful hymnist,

31:21.200 --> 31:24.400
Theseus was going to marry the beautiful Hippolyta.

31:25.200 --> 31:30.080
Theseus and Hippolyta walked through the city streets together, hand in hand.

31:32.160 --> 31:33.040
Four days.

31:34.000 --> 31:34.800
Said Theseus.

31:35.760 --> 31:38.640
It's a long time. I want to marry you now.

31:39.360 --> 31:40.960
Hippolyta smiled at him.

31:42.640 --> 31:45.840
Just then they saw Theseus's friend, Aegeus.

31:46.640 --> 31:50.320
He was walking quickly towards them, and he looked very angry.

31:51.200 --> 31:54.000
He was holding his daughter, Hermia, by her arm.

31:54.720 --> 31:56.160
She didn't want to go with him.

31:56.960 --> 31:59.600
Hermia was quite short with blonde hair.

32:00.320 --> 32:05.040
She was small and very pretty, but she was a strong person inside.

32:06.400 --> 32:09.120
Two young men followed Hermia and her father.

32:09.840 --> 32:14.480
They were Lysander and Demetrius, and they both loved Hermia.

32:15.600 --> 32:20.160
Lysander didn't have much money, but he was very handsome and kind.

32:21.040 --> 32:24.400
Demetrius was also handsome, and he was rich.

32:24.400 --> 32:28.480
But sometimes he was unkind, and he often got angry easily.

32:30.080 --> 32:32.960
Duke Theseus, you must help me.

32:32.960 --> 32:34.080
Said Aegeus.

32:34.080 --> 32:36.160
It's my daughter, Hermia.

32:37.040 --> 32:39.920
I chose this man, Demetrius, for her.

32:40.560 --> 32:44.320
He wants to marry her, but she won't do it.

32:44.320 --> 32:45.200
Why Hermia?

32:45.840 --> 32:47.280
Asked Theseus.

32:47.280 --> 32:48.720
Demetrius is a good man.

32:49.680 --> 32:51.680
Lysander is a good man too.

32:52.800 --> 32:53.680
Said Hermia.

32:54.320 --> 32:55.520
And I love him.

32:56.160 --> 32:59.680
I don't love Demetrius, and I will never marry him.

33:00.240 --> 33:02.320
I agree, said Lysander.

33:03.520 --> 33:06.000
Hermia's father likes Demetrius.

33:06.000 --> 33:06.720
That's fine.

33:07.520 --> 33:08.560
He can marry him.

33:09.280 --> 33:10.720
I'll take Hermia.

33:10.720 --> 33:13.280
I'll fight you for that, said Demetrius.

33:13.920 --> 33:16.880
Demetrius, you're forgetting about Helena.

33:17.440 --> 33:18.240
Said Hermia.

33:19.280 --> 33:21.760
Helena was Hermia's best friend.

33:22.320 --> 33:26.000
A few months before, Helena and Demetrius were in love.

33:26.640 --> 33:29.840
Then Demetrius suddenly fell in love with Hermia, instead.

33:30.560 --> 33:32.720
Now Demetrius never talked to Helena.

33:33.680 --> 33:36.160
Helena still loves you very much.

33:36.160 --> 33:36.960
Said Hermia.

33:37.600 --> 33:39.600
You broke her heart.

33:39.600 --> 33:41.360
That was a long time ago.

33:41.360 --> 33:42.320
Said Demetrius.

33:43.120 --> 33:43.920
It was a mistake.

33:44.800 --> 33:46.480
You're going to marry me, Hermia.

33:47.200 --> 33:49.200
Your father wants it, and I want it.

33:50.160 --> 33:51.840
Aegius turned to Theseus.

33:52.880 --> 33:55.120
Duke, please help me.

33:55.840 --> 33:57.280
I'm sorry, Hermia.

33:57.280 --> 33:58.880
You must listen to your father.

33:59.440 --> 34:00.240
Said Theseus.

34:01.440 --> 34:05.760
Later, Hermia and Lysander were alone together on a quiet street.

34:06.560 --> 34:08.320
Hermia felt afraid and sad.

34:08.960 --> 34:10.080
She began to cry.

34:12.080 --> 34:13.200
Lysander?

34:13.280 --> 34:14.880
I can't marry that man.

34:15.440 --> 34:16.720
I want to be with you.

34:18.480 --> 34:20.960
Lysander put his arms around her.

34:20.960 --> 34:21.840
He had a plan.

34:22.800 --> 34:24.640
We can run away together.

34:24.640 --> 34:25.760
He told Hermia.

34:26.320 --> 34:28.480
I have an aunt who lives far away.

34:29.040 --> 34:30.000
We can go there.

34:30.560 --> 34:31.760
We'll be safe with her.

34:32.480 --> 34:34.000
Then I can marry you.

34:35.040 --> 34:36.160
Meet me tomorrow night.

34:36.720 --> 34:39.360
We'll leave this city and we'll never come back.

34:40.000 --> 34:41.680
Of course I'll be there.

34:42.240 --> 34:43.440
Said Hermia.

34:43.440 --> 34:45.200
I'll go anywhere with you.

34:46.000 --> 34:47.840
Just then, they saw Helena.

34:48.640 --> 34:51.520
Helena was a tall, pretty girl with red hair.

34:52.240 --> 34:56.320
She often looked sad because she thought about Demetrius day and night.

34:57.440 --> 34:59.120
You're so lucky, Hermia.

34:59.760 --> 35:00.560
Helena said.

35:01.200 --> 35:05.040
Demetrius loves you, and he doesn't even want to look at me.

35:05.920 --> 35:07.600
And now he's going to marry you.

35:08.720 --> 35:11.360
Don't worry, said Lysander.

35:11.360 --> 35:13.040
That will never happen.

35:14.240 --> 35:16.080
They told Helena about their plan.

35:16.880 --> 35:18.160
I'll miss you, Helena.

35:18.720 --> 35:19.520
Hermia said.

35:20.080 --> 35:21.520
But think of it.

35:21.520 --> 35:22.720
I'll be far away.

35:23.280 --> 35:25.440
Demetrius will forget about me.

35:25.440 --> 35:26.800
He'll love you again.

35:27.360 --> 35:29.200
But Helena was not so sure.

35:30.320 --> 35:33.200
Hermia and Lysander walked away hand in hand.

35:33.920 --> 35:37.120
They were smiling and talking about their new life together.

35:37.920 --> 35:40.080
Helena sat alone and watched them.

35:40.880 --> 35:43.040
She thought about Demetrius for a long time.

35:44.160 --> 35:45.600
Then she had an idea.

35:46.880 --> 35:49.600
I'll tell Demetrius about Hermia's plan.

35:50.640 --> 35:52.640
He'll go to her, but he'll thank me.

35:53.200 --> 35:54.160
He'll talk to me.

35:54.800 --> 35:56.000
He'll smile at me.

35:56.800 --> 35:57.840
I'll tell him now.

35:58.560 --> 36:00.560
Helena ran to Demetrius' house.

36:05.200 --> 36:06.320
Listening activity.

36:08.240 --> 36:08.880
Example.

36:10.480 --> 36:12.960
I told Hermia to listen to her father.

36:15.280 --> 36:15.600
One.

36:17.200 --> 36:19.280
I will never marry Demetrius.

36:21.360 --> 36:21.600
Two.

36:23.280 --> 36:25.520
Hermia and I will run away together.

36:27.520 --> 36:27.840
Three.

36:29.360 --> 36:32.720
I'll tell Demetrius about Hermia and Lysander's plan.

36:34.560 --> 36:34.880
Four.

36:36.160 --> 36:38.480
I chose Demetrius for my daughter.

36:40.720 --> 36:41.120
Five.

36:42.240 --> 36:43.680
Hermia has to marry me.

36:44.400 --> 36:46.720
I wanted and her father wants it too.

36:51.280 --> 36:52.080
Chapter two.

36:53.040 --> 36:54.000
Trouble in the wood.

36:56.000 --> 36:59.600
In the wood two other people were unhappy because of love,

36:59.600 --> 37:00.960
but they weren't real people.

37:01.760 --> 37:03.920
They were the king and queen of the fairies.

37:04.480 --> 37:07.920
Beautiful Titania and dark handsome Oberon.

37:08.720 --> 37:12.800
They loved each other very much, but today they were arguing.

37:13.600 --> 37:17.120
Titania had a new servant, a beautiful Indian boy.

37:18.000 --> 37:22.000
Oberon needed a servant and he wanted the Indian boy for himself.

37:22.720 --> 37:24.080
Titania did not agree.

37:25.280 --> 37:28.000
In the evening they saw each other in the wood.

37:28.720 --> 37:31.200
Titania was walking with her fairies.

37:31.200 --> 37:33.040
They were dancing all around her.

37:34.000 --> 37:35.440
My queen.

37:36.560 --> 37:37.440
Said Oberon.

37:38.800 --> 37:41.040
Titania saw Oberon and turned away.

37:42.000 --> 37:43.840
I won't speak to you.

37:44.400 --> 37:44.960
She said.

37:46.560 --> 37:47.920
Why are we fighting?

37:48.480 --> 37:49.760
Just give me the boy.

37:50.240 --> 37:51.040
Said Oberon.

37:52.000 --> 37:54.000
I will never give him to you.

37:54.560 --> 37:55.040
Goodbye.

37:55.600 --> 37:56.560
Said Titania.

37:57.280 --> 37:59.280
The queen and her fairies walked away.

38:00.240 --> 38:02.080
Oberon felt very angry.

38:02.640 --> 38:05.120
Why won't she give me the boy?

38:05.120 --> 38:06.240
He said to himself.

38:07.440 --> 38:09.680
Why is she so cold to me?

38:10.320 --> 38:11.760
She'll be sorry for this.

38:12.720 --> 38:15.280
Then he remembered a special place in the wood.

38:15.920 --> 38:18.240
A small purple flower grew there.

38:18.880 --> 38:20.400
This flower was magic.

38:21.360 --> 38:23.200
Oberon had an idea.

38:24.000 --> 38:25.600
He called his servant Puck.

38:26.640 --> 38:27.840
Puck was a goblin.

38:28.720 --> 38:32.480
He was a very mischievous goblin and loved making trouble.

38:33.520 --> 38:35.760
Oberon told Puck about the flower.

38:36.960 --> 38:40.640
If you put the juice of this flower on someone's eyes,

38:40.640 --> 38:44.560
they will fall in love with anyone or anything.

38:45.600 --> 38:46.560
Find it for me, Puck.

38:47.200 --> 38:48.000
Said Oberon.

38:48.800 --> 38:50.880
I'll bring you that flower immediately.

38:51.440 --> 38:52.080
Said Puck.

38:52.640 --> 38:55.200
I can fly around the world in 40 minutes.

38:55.760 --> 38:56.720
Puck flew off.

38:57.840 --> 38:59.360
Oberon waited for Puck.

39:00.240 --> 39:03.280
Then suddenly a young man ran past him.

39:04.000 --> 39:06.240
He couldn't see Oberon because of his magic.

39:07.040 --> 39:09.600
A pretty young woman with red hair followed the man.

39:10.480 --> 39:12.480
She looked sad and tired.

39:13.600 --> 39:16.560
The two young people were Demetrius and Helena.

39:17.440 --> 39:20.480
Demetrius was looking for Hermia and Lysander.

39:21.120 --> 39:22.400
He wanted to stop them.

39:23.200 --> 39:25.680
Helena only wanted to be with Demetrius.

39:26.640 --> 39:29.120
Don't follow me, Demetrius shouted.

39:30.320 --> 39:31.520
Go home, Helena.

39:32.320 --> 39:33.520
Please, Demetrius.

39:34.080 --> 39:34.800
Said Helena.

39:35.360 --> 39:36.560
I want to come with you.

39:37.600 --> 39:39.440
Where are Lysander and Hermia?

39:40.320 --> 39:41.280
Said Demetrius.

39:41.920 --> 39:45.920
I'll kill Lysander and I'll bring Hermia back to Athens.

39:45.920 --> 39:47.760
She'll be my wife, not his.

39:48.640 --> 39:49.520
Where are they?

39:51.120 --> 39:52.160
I don't know.

39:52.800 --> 39:53.600
Said Helena.

39:54.160 --> 39:56.400
I only know that they are in this wood.

39:57.120 --> 40:00.480
Please, I only want to be near you.

40:00.480 --> 40:02.000
I don't love you.

40:02.000 --> 40:03.360
Said Demetrius.

40:03.360 --> 40:05.040
I don't even want to look at you.

40:05.840 --> 40:07.200
Helena began to cry.

40:08.160 --> 40:09.920
I love you, Demetrius.

40:11.200 --> 40:11.760
She said.

40:13.360 --> 40:15.680
Demetrius pushed Helena and she fell.

40:16.400 --> 40:18.240
Don't follow me.

40:18.240 --> 40:22.000
He said, please don't come near me.

40:22.880 --> 40:23.680
He ran away.

40:24.720 --> 40:26.320
Helena slowly stood up.

40:27.440 --> 40:29.200
I need to be near him.

40:29.760 --> 40:30.320
She thought.

40:31.520 --> 40:33.360
She followed Demetrius into the wood.

40:34.400 --> 40:35.920
Oberon watched Helena.

40:36.560 --> 40:38.400
That poor, sweet lady.

40:38.960 --> 40:40.080
He said to himself.

40:41.520 --> 40:42.640
He wanted to help her.

40:43.280 --> 40:44.880
Just then, Puck returned.

40:45.440 --> 40:46.800
He had the magic flower.

40:47.760 --> 40:49.360
Oberon smiled.

40:49.360 --> 40:51.120
Excellent, he said.

40:52.400 --> 40:54.400
Titania will go to sleep soon.

40:55.040 --> 40:58.800
I'll find her and put the juice of this flower on her eyes.

40:59.520 --> 41:04.240
She'll wake up and she'll fall in love with anything.

41:05.600 --> 41:08.960
Perhaps a bear or a bird or even a monkey.

41:09.600 --> 41:10.480
It doesn't matter.

41:11.520 --> 41:14.800
When she sees it, she will love it.

41:17.520 --> 41:18.320
He laughed.

41:19.040 --> 41:20.400
Then he remembered Helena.

41:21.280 --> 41:23.760
I saw a young man and a young woman here.

41:23.760 --> 41:24.960
He said to Puck.

41:26.000 --> 41:26.960
They're from Athens.

41:27.760 --> 41:30.080
The woman loves the man, but he hates her.

41:30.640 --> 41:33.120
Put the juice of this flower on the man's eyes.

41:33.680 --> 41:35.040
He'll fall in love with her.

41:35.760 --> 41:36.480
Can you do this?

41:37.120 --> 41:38.720
Of course, said Puck.

41:39.120 --> 41:39.920
It's easy.

41:40.480 --> 41:42.880
I'll look for the two young people from Athens.

41:44.080 --> 41:44.880
He flew away.

41:45.840 --> 41:48.400
Later, Oberon found Titania.

41:49.280 --> 41:51.680
She was sleeping on a bed of flowers near the river.

41:52.560 --> 41:55.760
Oberon put the juice of the flower on Titania's eyes.

41:56.720 --> 41:59.440
Soon, you'll fall in love.

42:00.000 --> 42:00.800
He said to her,

42:01.840 --> 42:04.800
I hope that you will love something horrible.

42:09.600 --> 42:10.160
Fairies.

42:12.240 --> 42:15.760
Countries all over the world have stories about fairies.

42:16.480 --> 42:19.840
And some of these stories are very, very old.

42:21.280 --> 42:24.240
In these stories, fairies looked like people,

42:24.880 --> 42:27.280
but they could fly and use magic.

42:28.480 --> 42:30.880
Sometimes they were bigger than people.

42:31.600 --> 42:35.680
Sometimes they were smaller, and they had no wings.

42:37.520 --> 42:41.440
People believed that fairies could do good things and bad things,

42:42.000 --> 42:45.040
that they could sometimes hurt people or animals.

42:46.160 --> 42:50.640
They also believed that people lost their way in woods because of fairies.

42:52.480 --> 42:58.560
People even thought that fairies sometimes stole babies and children and kept them.

43:00.160 --> 43:05.920
In a mid-summer night's dream, Titania and Oberon have a child with them from India

43:05.920 --> 43:07.200
who is not a fairy.

43:09.280 --> 43:15.120
Sometimes people did strange things because they wanted to be safe from fairy magic.

43:16.320 --> 43:20.160
They often kept some cold iron in their houses

43:20.160 --> 43:22.880
because they thought that fairies were afraid of it.

43:24.640 --> 43:28.240
When they were in a wood, they sometimes carried bread with them.

43:29.440 --> 43:34.480
People with houses on a fairy road kept their doors open all night.

43:36.480 --> 43:40.800
Old stories all agree that only animals can see fairies.

43:41.680 --> 43:43.360
People usually can't see them.

43:44.320 --> 43:49.920
But if fairies want to appear, they can use their magic and people can see them.

43:51.440 --> 43:57.360
In a mid-summer night's dream, no one can see Oberon and Puck except other fairies.

43:58.400 --> 44:03.760
Later you will read that one person, bottom, can see Titania and her fairies.

44:05.040 --> 44:07.840
This is because she wants to appear to him.

44:08.160 --> 44:13.120
Through the years, people's ideas about fairies slowly changed.

44:13.120 --> 44:19.600
In stories, fairies became smaller and prettier, and they usually had wings.

44:19.600 --> 44:23.200
They were good and never hurt people.

44:23.200 --> 44:26.560
This is our idea of fairies today.

44:27.520 --> 44:29.440
Do you believe in fairies?

44:29.440 --> 44:36.000
Be careful if you are in a wood and take some bread and cold iron with you.

44:36.000 --> 44:50.160
In another part of the wood, Lysander and Hermia were lost.

44:51.120 --> 44:55.840
They walked together for hours through the trees, but they couldn't find a way out of the wood.

44:56.720 --> 44:58.320
They both felt very tired.

44:58.880 --> 44:59.840
Their feet hurt.

45:00.720 --> 45:04.080
They wanted to sleep, but they continued walking.

45:05.040 --> 45:08.400
Finally, they stopped at a quiet place near a river.

45:10.480 --> 45:12.320
Let's rest here, Hermia.

45:12.960 --> 45:16.160
Said Lysander, we can start again tomorrow.

45:17.440 --> 45:19.280
That's a good idea.

45:19.280 --> 45:24.320
Said Hermia, she lay down on the soft grass by the side of the river.

45:25.520 --> 45:27.280
Good night, Lysander.

45:27.280 --> 45:30.240
She said, and she fell asleep immediately.

45:31.440 --> 45:33.280
Lysander looked at her for a moment.

45:34.480 --> 45:37.040
I'll always love her.

45:37.040 --> 45:37.600
He thought.

45:38.800 --> 45:42.640
Soon he was asleep too, not far from Hermia.

45:43.520 --> 45:48.720
At the same time, Puck was flying through the trees with the magic flower in his hand.

45:49.840 --> 45:55.680
He was looking for a young man and a young woman from Athens, but he couldn't see anyone.

45:56.960 --> 45:58.400
Where are they?

45:58.400 --> 45:58.960
He thought.

45:59.600 --> 46:01.920
Oberon will be angry if I don't find them.

46:02.800 --> 46:05.200
Then he saw Lysander and Hermia.

46:06.000 --> 46:08.560
At last, he said.

46:09.200 --> 46:12.320
A young man and young woman from Athens.

46:12.320 --> 46:14.800
He flew down and looked at Lysander.

46:16.080 --> 46:18.880
Now, what did Oberon say?

46:18.880 --> 46:20.000
He asked himself.

46:20.960 --> 46:25.680
She loves him, but he hates her.

46:25.680 --> 46:27.520
Well, that will change.

46:28.400 --> 46:32.400
Puck put the juice of the magic flower on Lysander's eyes.

46:33.120 --> 46:34.720
There, he said.

46:35.440 --> 46:39.680
He'll wake up, he'll see her, and he'll fall in love.

46:40.560 --> 46:41.440
He flew away.

46:42.880 --> 46:45.760
Demetrius was still looking for Hermia and Lysander.

46:46.640 --> 46:49.040
Poor Helena was still following Demetrius.

46:49.840 --> 46:55.840
Sometimes Demetrius ran too quickly, and sometimes he shouted at her,

46:55.920 --> 46:57.520
but she still followed him.

46:58.720 --> 47:03.280
They came to the place by the river, where Hermia and Lysander were sleeping.

47:04.160 --> 47:08.480
It was very dark, and so Demetrius and Helena didn't see them.

47:09.680 --> 47:11.840
Please wait for me to meet Demetrius.

47:12.560 --> 47:13.440
Helena said.

47:14.320 --> 47:18.560
For the last time, Helena, go home, Demetrius shouted.

47:19.360 --> 47:20.640
He ran away quickly.

47:21.920 --> 47:24.160
This time, Helena didn't follow him.

47:24.960 --> 47:26.160
She was too tired.

47:26.960 --> 47:29.440
She sat down on a rock and looked at the river.

47:30.320 --> 47:32.000
He's running away from me.

47:32.960 --> 47:33.920
She thought.

47:33.920 --> 47:35.360
And he's running to her.

47:36.400 --> 47:37.440
Lucky Hermia.

47:38.480 --> 47:39.840
Then she saw Lysander.

47:40.560 --> 47:41.920
He was sleeping on the grass.

47:42.640 --> 47:44.240
She was very surprised.

47:45.200 --> 47:47.760
Lysander, what are you doing here?

47:48.560 --> 47:49.440
Are you all right?

47:50.080 --> 47:50.720
She asked.

47:51.600 --> 47:53.920
Lysander opened his eyes slowly.

47:54.560 --> 47:58.240
The most beautiful woman in the world was looking at him.

47:58.960 --> 47:59.920
It was Helena.

48:01.200 --> 48:02.960
She's so lovely.

48:03.920 --> 48:05.120
She's wonderful.

48:05.680 --> 48:06.240
He thought.

48:07.120 --> 48:08.880
Why didn't I see it before?

48:10.480 --> 48:13.120
He remembered that Helena loved Demetrius.

48:14.000 --> 48:15.840
Suddenly he got very angry.

48:16.800 --> 48:18.160
We can't play, Santa.

48:18.720 --> 48:19.440
Said Helena.

48:21.040 --> 48:22.560
Lysander stood up quickly.

48:23.520 --> 48:24.960
Anything for you, Helena.

48:25.920 --> 48:26.960
Where is Demetrius?

48:27.600 --> 48:28.400
I'll kill him.

48:29.520 --> 48:33.120
Helena didn't understand Lysander's strange words.

48:33.120 --> 48:35.280
Or the strange look in his eyes.

48:36.000 --> 48:36.880
No, Lysander.

48:37.360 --> 48:39.440
Don't be angry with Demetrius.

48:39.440 --> 48:40.000
She said.

48:40.720 --> 48:44.320
I know he loves Hermia, but she only wants you.

48:45.520 --> 48:46.160
Hermia?

48:47.040 --> 48:48.480
Said Lysander.

48:48.480 --> 48:50.400
I'm not interested in Hermia.

48:50.960 --> 48:51.840
I love you.

48:52.720 --> 48:53.440
Not her.

48:54.160 --> 48:55.840
That's not funny, Lysander.

48:56.400 --> 48:58.080
Don't joke about that.

48:58.080 --> 48:58.880
Said Helena.

48:59.440 --> 49:00.480
It's not a joke.

49:01.040 --> 49:02.000
I love you.

49:03.200 --> 49:04.160
Said Lysander.

49:05.120 --> 49:06.960
Helena got very angry.

49:07.920 --> 49:09.040
This is too much.

49:09.600 --> 49:12.000
First Demetrius ran away from me.

49:12.000 --> 49:13.360
Now you're laughing at me.

49:14.320 --> 49:16.320
Helena turned and ran.

49:16.320 --> 49:17.440
No, wait.

49:17.440 --> 49:18.480
Said Lysander.

49:19.440 --> 49:20.880
Then he remembered Hermia.

49:21.600 --> 49:23.280
She was still asleep on the grass.

49:24.080 --> 49:25.360
Lysander looked at her.

49:26.400 --> 49:28.560
Did I really love this girl?

49:30.240 --> 49:31.360
She's nothing.

49:32.320 --> 49:32.960
He thought.

49:34.080 --> 49:35.840
He followed Helena into the wood.

49:37.440 --> 49:40.160
Later, Hermia woke up with a scream.

49:42.640 --> 49:45.440
Lysander, I had a bad dream.

49:45.440 --> 49:46.000
She said.

49:47.040 --> 49:48.800
Lysander, where are you?

49:49.680 --> 49:51.600
Lysander didn't answer her.

49:52.560 --> 49:55.040
She couldn't see him or hear him anywhere.

49:55.840 --> 49:56.640
He was gone.

49:57.680 --> 49:59.280
She suddenly felt afraid.

50:00.480 --> 50:01.600
What happened to him?

50:02.400 --> 50:03.360
Is he in danger?

50:04.160 --> 50:04.880
Where is he?

50:06.000 --> 50:06.640
She thought.

50:07.440 --> 50:08.800
I have to find him.

50:13.200 --> 50:14.000
Chapter 4.

50:14.880 --> 50:15.680
The Actors.

50:16.560 --> 50:18.720
By the river on her bed of flowers,

50:18.720 --> 50:20.720
Queen Titania was sleeping.

50:21.600 --> 50:24.560
The juice of the magic flowers on her eyes.

50:25.120 --> 50:26.400
Puck watched her.

50:27.440 --> 50:31.040
Soon she'll wake up and she'll fall in love.

50:31.040 --> 50:32.400
He thought.

50:32.400 --> 50:37.440
Will it be a bear or a dog or a bird?

50:37.840 --> 50:39.120
Well, it happens.

50:39.120 --> 50:40.880
I must tell Oberon.

50:41.920 --> 50:44.240
Suddenly he heard voices.

50:44.480 --> 50:50.800
A group of men from Athens were talking very close to the place where Titania was sleeping.

50:51.680 --> 50:53.440
Puck decided to listen to them.

50:54.720 --> 50:56.400
The men were practicing a play.

50:57.200 --> 51:01.520
They wanted to show this play at Thesis and Hippolytus wedding.

51:02.560 --> 51:04.720
These men weren't really actors.

51:05.280 --> 51:06.800
This was just their hobby.

51:08.080 --> 51:09.520
They all had different jobs.

51:10.480 --> 51:12.000
One of the men was a tailor.

51:12.800 --> 51:14.000
One was a carpenter.

51:14.640 --> 51:15.520
One had a shop.

51:16.160 --> 51:18.000
Others built walls and houses.

51:18.880 --> 51:20.880
They were not the best actors in the world.

51:21.760 --> 51:23.920
In fact, they were very bad.

51:24.960 --> 51:28.480
But they loved acting and they always tried their best.

51:30.640 --> 51:34.080
One of the actors, bottom, loved acting the most.

51:34.960 --> 51:39.840
He was a large kind man with a round face who always smiled.

51:40.800 --> 51:43.840
Bottom, you will be the hero of this play.

51:44.800 --> 51:46.720
Set his friend Peter Quince.

51:47.120 --> 51:50.000
There is also a lady and a lion.

51:51.040 --> 51:52.720
I can be all of them.

51:53.200 --> 51:54.240
Set bottom.

51:54.640 --> 52:01.120
I'll be a handsome hero and a pretty lady and a dangerous lion.

52:02.320 --> 52:04.080
Thesis will love it.

52:04.480 --> 52:06.080
You'll be the hero bottom.

52:06.800 --> 52:07.440
Set Peter.

52:08.080 --> 52:08.880
Only.

52:10.080 --> 52:10.880
The hero.

52:11.600 --> 52:13.920
Now go behind that tree and practice.

52:15.040 --> 52:16.480
I'll call you when we need you.

52:17.840 --> 52:19.920
Bottom went behind a large tree.

52:20.640 --> 52:21.600
Puck was watching.

52:22.720 --> 52:24.320
Is this the hero?

52:24.960 --> 52:25.520
He thought.

52:26.400 --> 52:27.120
He laughed.

52:29.760 --> 52:31.840
I have a wonderful idea.

52:33.360 --> 52:34.720
Puck used his magic.

52:35.840 --> 52:38.240
Bottom suddenly felt very strange.

52:39.040 --> 52:40.400
His ears began to grow.

52:41.040 --> 52:42.880
His nose got bigger and bigger.

52:43.440 --> 52:48.400
His teeth got larger and hair began to grow all over his face.

52:50.240 --> 52:51.360
What's happening?

52:52.720 --> 52:56.080
He said and his voice was very strange.

52:57.120 --> 53:00.880
Soon, poor bottom had a large ugly donkey's head.

53:01.600 --> 53:02.640
Puck smiled.

53:04.320 --> 53:05.360
Where's the hero?

53:06.480 --> 53:07.680
Called Peter Quince.

53:08.720 --> 53:09.280
Bottom.

53:10.000 --> 53:10.720
We need you.

53:11.760 --> 53:14.000
Bottom came out from behind the tree.

53:15.120 --> 53:15.920
Here I am.

53:16.880 --> 53:18.720
He said in his strange voice.

53:19.600 --> 53:20.880
I'm the hero.

53:22.080 --> 53:23.360
Where's my lady?

53:23.920 --> 53:25.840
His friends screamed.

53:27.280 --> 53:28.480
He's a monster.

53:29.200 --> 53:29.760
They said.

53:30.480 --> 53:31.920
They ran away quickly.

53:33.200 --> 53:33.600
Bottom.

53:34.160 --> 53:35.440
Look at yourself.

53:35.440 --> 53:36.560
Said Peter Quince.

53:37.200 --> 53:38.720
And then he followed the others.

53:39.760 --> 53:41.680
Bottom couldn't see himself.

53:43.280 --> 53:44.880
Why are they running?

53:46.640 --> 53:47.200
He thought.

53:48.480 --> 53:50.320
Are they playing a joke?

53:51.680 --> 53:53.360
I know that you're joking.

53:54.320 --> 53:55.840
Bottom shouted.

53:55.840 --> 53:57.120
I'm not afraid.

53:57.680 --> 53:58.480
Do you hear me?

53:59.040 --> 54:00.320
I feel fine.

54:01.040 --> 54:01.760
I'll sing.

54:02.720 --> 54:04.000
Baa baa.

54:04.000 --> 54:05.280
Black sheep.

54:05.280 --> 54:06.960
Are you anyone?

54:08.240 --> 54:09.600
No sign.

54:09.600 --> 54:11.040
No sign.

54:11.040 --> 54:13.120
Three bags full.

54:14.800 --> 54:16.960
And bottom began to sing loudly.

54:17.520 --> 54:19.200
It was a terrible noise.

54:19.920 --> 54:22.080
He walked up and down and sang.

54:22.880 --> 54:26.160
Soon, he came to the place where Titania was asleep.

54:26.960 --> 54:28.240
Her eyes opened.

54:29.360 --> 54:30.240
That song?

54:31.120 --> 54:32.160
She thought.

54:32.800 --> 54:33.600
That voice.

54:34.640 --> 54:35.920
It's beautiful.

54:37.200 --> 54:38.320
Then she saw bottom.

54:39.200 --> 54:42.080
She looked at bottom's ugly long ears

54:42.080 --> 54:44.560
and his long nose and his big teeth.

54:45.520 --> 54:48.800
She thought that he was the most beautiful person in the world.

54:50.000 --> 54:51.760
Titania stood up quickly.

54:52.400 --> 54:53.120
Sing again.

54:53.680 --> 54:54.160
She said.

54:54.640 --> 54:55.840
Please sing again.

54:56.560 --> 54:58.480
Your song is so lovely.

54:59.040 --> 55:00.640
And you are so handsome.

55:01.280 --> 55:02.400
I don't know you.

55:02.400 --> 55:03.440
But I love you.

55:04.320 --> 55:06.240
Bottom was very surprised.

55:07.920 --> 55:08.240
Wait.

55:09.840 --> 55:11.680
Do you think I'm handsome?

55:13.280 --> 55:14.320
Do you love me?

55:14.960 --> 55:15.520
He said.

55:16.480 --> 55:19.280
He smiled and showed his big yellow teeth.

55:21.520 --> 55:23.760
This is a dream.

55:24.240 --> 55:25.280
He thought.

55:25.280 --> 55:28.560
And it's a very good dream.

55:29.440 --> 55:31.920
Yes. Of course I love you.

55:32.480 --> 55:33.440
Titania said.

55:34.080 --> 55:36.800
Please, stay here in the wood with me.

55:37.440 --> 55:39.680
I am the queen of the fairies.

55:39.680 --> 55:42.000
My servants will bring you anything.

55:43.200 --> 55:45.520
Titania called her fairy servants.

55:46.400 --> 55:49.200
Suddenly, there were fairies everywhere.

55:49.200 --> 55:51.600
They flew and danced around Titania.

55:52.480 --> 55:54.480
This is my love.

55:54.960 --> 55:56.240
She said to them.

55:56.240 --> 55:58.560
Bring him food and flowers.

55:59.520 --> 56:01.440
Bottom couldn't believe his luck.

56:02.160 --> 56:06.320
He walked through the wood hand in hand with beautiful Titania.

56:07.280 --> 56:09.600
Puck laughed and laughed.

56:09.600 --> 56:10.960
He flew through the trees.

56:11.680 --> 56:13.280
Then he found Oberon.

56:13.280 --> 56:15.200
And he told him the whole story.

56:16.240 --> 56:17.520
This is wonderful.

56:18.320 --> 56:19.120
Said Oberon.

56:20.000 --> 56:20.640
He laughed.

56:25.360 --> 56:30.960
The queen of the fairies is in love with an ugly monster.

56:31.520 --> 56:32.960
Good work, Puck.

